properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 9 at 3:28AM CST until February 9 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Winter Storm to Impact Portions of Northern Iowa Today...

.Snow will continue develop over northern Iowa Early this
morning. The snowfall rates will be moderate to heavy at times yet
this morning, leading to a quick deterioration in travel
conditions over far northern Iowa. Snow accumulations will be
mainly confined to areas north of Highway 20. A transition to
freezing drizzle or freezing rain may occur early this morning and
may cause some minor ice accumulations north of Highway 30.
Increasing north wind today may lead to some blowing and drifting
of snow especially in far northern Iowa where less freezing
drizzle and rain occurs.

* WHAT...Moderate to heavy snow and light mixed precipitation
expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 7 inches and ice
accumulations of a light glaze.

* WHERE...Portions of north central Iowa including the northern
portion of Interstate 35.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 3 PM CST Today.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult with conditions
deteriorating quickly after midnight tonight. This will
include Interstate 35 across northern Iowa.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
